# Component Workflow Reference

Reference document for the `/create`, `/enhance`, and `/publish` workflows. The slash commands
in `.cursor/commands/` are the entry points; this rule provides the sub-agent
strategy, feasibility decision tree, and quality gate checklist that those
commands and their skills rely on.

## Workflow Entry Points

| Command | File | Skill |
|---------|------|-------|
| `/create <component>` | `.cursor/commands/create.md` | `.cursor/skills/master-orchestrator.md` |
| `/enhance <component>` | `.cursor/commands/enhance.md` | Phase skills listed in command |
| `/publish` | `.cursor/commands/publish.md` | `.cursor/skills/publish.md` |

## Available Agents

| Agent | File | Purpose |
|-------|------|---------|
| `code-reviewer` | `.cursor/agents/code-reviewer.md` | Read-only quality audit against conventions and pitfalls |
| `web-source-analyzer` | `.cursor/agents/web-source-analyzer.md` | Extract web component API from local twigs-react source |

## Environment Notes

- **Figma MCP and Cursor Figma plugin are pre-enabled.**
- `/create` must use those existing integrations for design extraction when
  Figma references are provided.
- Do not add or evaluate external MCP integrations for this workflow.

## .cursor-Only Modification Mode

When the request is workflow maintenance (commands/skills/rules/agents):

- Modify `.cursor/` files only
- Do not edit `src/`, `docs/`, `lib/`, or runtime component code
- Keep quality gates and release standards intact

